obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9047)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9047&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Cable Television`
  line `Networks (Regulation) Act, 1995.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 29th day of September, 1994.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9048)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9048&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) "authorised officer" means, within his local limits of jurisdiction,--`
  line
  line `(i) a District Magistrate, or`
  line
  line `(ii) a Sub-divisional Magistrate, or`
  line
  line `(iii) a Commissioner of Police,`
  line
  line `and includes any other officer notified in the Official Gazette, by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, to be an authorised officer for such local limits of jurisdiction as may be determined by`
  line `that Government;]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ai) "Authority" means the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997);`
  line
  line `(aii) "Broadcaster" means a person or a group of persons, or body corporate, or any organisation`
  line `or body providing programming services and includes his or its authorised distribution agencies;`
  line
  line `(aiii) "cable operator" means any person who provides cable service through a cable television`
  line `network or otherwise controls or is responsible for the management and operation of a cable`
  line `television network and fulfils the prescribed eligibility criteria and conditions;]`
  line
  line `(b) "cable service" means the transmission by cables of programmes including re-transmission by`
  line `cables of any broadcast television signals;`
  line
  line `(c) "cable television network" means any system consisting of a set of closed transmission paths`
  line `and associated signal generation, control and distribution equipment, designed to provide cable`
  line `service for reception by multiple subscribers;`
  line
  line `(d) "company" means a company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(e) "person" means--`
  line
  line `(i) an individual who is a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) an association of individuals or body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, whose`
  line `members are citizens of India;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(iii) a company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(ei) "post" means a post and includes a pole, tower, standard, stay, strut, cabinet, pillar or any`
  line `above ground contrivance for carrying, suspending or supporting any network infrastructure facility;]`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "programme" means any television broadcast and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) exhibition of films, features, dramas, advertisements and serials ^5`
  line ***;
  line
  line `(ii) any audio or visual or audio-visual live performance or presentation,`
  line
  line `and the expression programming service shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(gi) "public authority" means any authority, body or institution of local self-government`
  line
  line `constituted or established by or under--`
  line
  line `(i) the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) any law made by Parliament;`
  line
  line `(iii) any law made by a State Legislature;`
  line
  line `(iv) any notification issued or order made by the appropriate Government,`
  line
  line `and includes any--`
  line
  line `(v) body owned, controlled or substantially financed; or`
  line
  line `(vi) non-governmental organisation substantially financed,`
  line
  line `directly or indirectly by funds provided by the appropriate Government;]`
  line
  line `(h) "registering authority" means such authority as the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, specify to perform the functions of the registering authority under this`
  line `Act ^4`
  line `[within such local limits of jurisdiction as may be determined by that Government];`
  line
  line `(i) "subscriber" means ^6`
  line `[any individual, or association of individuals, or a company, or any other`
  line `organisation or body]who receives the signals of cable television network at a place ^7`
  line `[indicated by`
  line `him or it] to the cable operator, without further transmitting it to any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s. 2, for clause (aa) (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s. 2, for sub-clause (iii) (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `5. The words "through video cassette recorders or video cassette players" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "a person" (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "indicated by him" (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9049)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Cable television network not to be operated except after registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9049&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `No person shall operate`
  line `a cable television network unless he is registered as a cable operator under this Act.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9050)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Registration as cable operator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 4, ibid.,for section 4 (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9050&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[4. Registration as cable operator.--(1) Any person who is desirous of operating or is operating a`
  line `cable television network may apply for registration or renewal of registration, as a cable operator to the`
  line `registering authority.`
  line
  line `(2) The cable operator shall fulfil such eligibility criteria and conditions as may be prescribed and`
  line `different eligibility criteria may be prescribed for different categories of cable operators.`
  line
  line `(3) On and from the date of issue of notification under section 4A, no new registration in a State, city,`
  line `town or area notified under that section shall be granted to any cable operator who does not undertake to`
  line `transmit or re-transmit channels in an encrypted form through a digital addressable system.`
  line
  line `(4) An application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and be accompanied by such`
  line `documents and fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of the application, the registering authority shall satisfy itself that the applicant has`
  line `furnished all the required information prescribed under sub-section (4) and on being so satisfied, register`
  line `the applicant as a cable operator and grant him a certificate of registration or renew its registration, as the`
  line `case may be, subject to such terms and conditions as may be prescribed under sub-section (6):`
  line
  line `Provided that the registering authority may, if it is satisfied that the applicant does not fulfil the`
  line `eligibility criteria and conditions prescribed under sub-section (2) or the application is not accompanied`
  line `by necessary documents or fees as prescribed under sub-section (4), and for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, by order, refuse to grant its registration or renewal, as the case may be, and communicate the`
  line `same to the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the applicant may prefer an appeal against the order of the registering authority`
  line `refusing grant or renewal of registration to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to the compliance of eligibility criteria for registration of cable operators, the`
  line `Central Government may prescribe, having regard to the interests of the sovereignty and integrity of`
  line `India, the security of the State, friendly relations with foreign States, public order, decency or morality,`
  line `foreign relation or contempt of court, defamation or incitement to an offence, such terms and conditions`
  line `of registration including additional criteria or conditions to be fulfilled by the cable operator.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government may suspend or revoke the registration granted under sub-section (5) if`
  line `the cable operator violates one or more of the terms and conditions of such registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order of suspension or revocation shall be made without giving reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard to the cable operator.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (9051)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 5
  title `Transmission of programmes through digital addressable systems, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s. 5, for section 4A (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9051&sectionno=4A&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[4A. Transmission of programmes through digital addressable systems, etc.-- (1) Where the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, make it obligatory for every cable operator to transmit or re-transmit programmes`
  line `of any channel in an encrypted form through a digital addressable system with effect from such date as`
  line `may be specified in the notification and different dates may be specified for different States, cities, towns`
  line `or areas, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the date specified in the notification shall not be earlier than six months from the date of`
  line `issue of such notification to enable the cable operators in different States, cities, towns or areas to install`
  line `the equipment required for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may prescribe appropriate measures and take such steps as it may`
  line `consider necessary for implementation of the notification issued under sub-section(1).`
  line
  line `(3) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, and if not`
  line `otherwise specified by the Authority, it may direct the Authority to specify, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, one or more free-to-air channels to be included in the package of channels forming basic service`
  line `tier and any one or more such channels may be specified, in the notification, genre-wise for providing a`
  line `programme mix of entertainment, information, education and such other programmes and fix the tariff for`
  line `basic service tier which shall be offered by the cable operators to the consumers and the consumer shall`
  line `have the option to subscribe to any such tier:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cable operator shall also offer the channels in the basic service tier on a la carte`
  line `basis to the subscriber at a tariff specified under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government or the Authority may specify in the notification referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3), the number of free-to-air channels to be included in the package of channels forming basic service tier for the purposes of that sub-section and different numbers may be specified for different`
  line `States, cities, towns or areas, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) It shall be obligatory for every cable operator to publicise the prescribed information including but`
  line `not limited to subscription rates, standards of quality of service and mechanism for redressal of`
  line `subscribers' grievances in such manner and at such periodic intervals as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government or the Authority for the benefit of the subscriber.`
  line
  line `(6) The cable operator shall not require any subscriber to have a receiver set of a particular type to`
  line `receive signals of cable television network:`
  line
  line `Provided that the subscriber shall use a digital addressable system to be attached to his receiver set for`
  line `receiving programmes transmitted on any channel.`
  line
  line `(7) Every cable operator shall provide such information relating to its cable services and networks in`
  line `such format and at such periodic intervals to the Central Government or the State Governments or the`
  line `Authority or their authorised representatives, as may be specified by them from time to time.`
  line
  line `(8) All actions taken by the Central Government or the Authority in pursuance of the provisions of`
  line `this section as they stood immediately before the 25th day of October, 2011shall continue to remain in`
  line `force till such actions are modified as per the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "addressable system" means an electronic device (which includes hardware and its associated`
  line `software) or more than one electronic device put in an integrated system through which signals of`
  line `cable television network can be sent in encrypted form, which can be decoded by the device or`
  line `devices, having an activated Conditional Access System at the premises of the subscriber within the`
  line `limits of authorisation made, through the Conditional Access System and the subscriber management`
  line `system, on the explicit choice and request of such subscriber, by the cable operator to the subscriber;`
  line
  line `(b) "basic service tier" means a package of free-to-air channels to be offered by a cable operator`
  line `to a subscriber with an option to subscribe, for a single price to subscribers of the area in which his`
  line `cable television network is providing service;`
  line
  line `(c) "encrypted", in respect of a signal of cable television network, means the changing of such`
  line `signal in a systematic way so that the signal would be unintelligible without use of an addressable`
  line `system and the expression "unencrypted" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(d) "free-to-air channel", in respect of a cable television network, means a channel for which no`
  line `subscription fee is to be paid by the cable operator to the broadcaster for its re-transmission on cable;`
  line
  line `(e) "pay channel", in respect of a cable television network, means a channel for which`
  line `subscription fees is to be paid to the broadcaster by the cable operator and due authorisation needs to`
  line `be taken from the broadcaster for its re-transmission on cable;`
  line
  line `(f) "subscriber management system" means a system or device which stores the subscriber`
  line `records and details with respect to name, address and other information regarding the hardware being`
  line `utilised by the subscriber, channels or bouquets of channels subscribed to by the subscriber, price of`
  line `such channels or bouquets of channels as defined in the system, the activation or deactivation dates`
  line `and time for any channel or bouquets of channels, a log of all actions performed on a subscriber's`
  line `record, invoices raised on each subscriber and the amounts paid or discount allowed to the subscriber`
  line `for each billing period.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (9052)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 6
  title `Right of way for cable operators and permission by public authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s. 5, for section 4A (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9052&sectionno=4B&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[4B. Right of way for cable operators and permission by public authority.--(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, any cable operator entitled for providing cable services may, from time to time, lay`
  line `and establish cables and erect posts under, over, along, across, in or upon any immovable property vested`
  line `in or under the control or management of a public authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Any public authority under whose control or management any immovable property is vested may,`
  line `on receipt of a request from a cable operator permit the cable operator to do all or any of the following`
  line `acts, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to place and maintain underground cables or posts; and`
  line
  line `(b) to enter on the property, from time to time, in order to place, examine, repair, alter or remove`
  line `such cables or posts.`
  line
  line `(3) The facility of right of way under this section for laying underground cables, and erecting posts,`
  line `shall be available to all cable operators subject to the obligation of reinstatement or restoration of the`
  line `property or payment of reinstatement or restoration charges in respect thereof at the option of the public`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(4) When a public authority in public interest considers it necessary and expedient that the`
  line `underground cable or post placed by any cable operator under the provisions of this section should be`
  line `removed or shifted or its position altered, it may require the cable operator to remove it or shift it or alter`
  line `its position, as the case may be, at its own cost in the timeframe indicated by the public authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may lay down appropriate guidelines to enable the State Governments to`
  line `put in place an appropriate mechanism for speedy clearance of requests from cable operators for laying`
  line `cables or erecting posts on any property vested in, or under the control or management of, any public`
  line `authority and for settlement of disputes, including refusal of permission by the public authority.`
  line
  line `(6) Any permission granted by a public authority under this section may be given subject to such`
  line `reasonable conditions as that public authority thinks fit to impose as to the payment of any expenses, or`
  line `time or mode of execution of any work, or as to any other matter connected with or related to any work`
  line `undertaken by the cable operator in exercise of those rights.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall confer any right upon any cable operator other than that of user for`
  line `the purpose only of laying underground cable or erecting posts or maintaining them.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9053)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Programme code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by Act 36 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9053&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No person shall transmit or re-transmit through a cable service any`
  line `programme unless such programme is in conformity with the prescribed programme code.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9054)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Advertisement code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9054&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No person shall transmit or re-transmit through a cable service any`
  line `advertisement unless such advertisement is in conformity with the prescribed advertisement code.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9055)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Maintenance of register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9055&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every cable operator shall maintain a register in the prescribed form`
  line `indicating therein in brief the programmes transmitted or re-transmitted through the cable service during a`
  line `month and such register shall be maintained by the cable operator for a period of one year after the actual`
  line `transmission or re-transmission of the said programmes.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9056)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Compulsory transmission of certain channels.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s. 6, for section 8 (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9056&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[8. Compulsory transmission of certain channels. (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify the names of Doordarshan channels or the channels operated`
  line `by or on behalf of Parliament, to be mandatorily carried by the cable operators in their cable service and`
  line `the manner of reception and re-transmission of such channels:`
  line
  line `Provided that in areas where digital addressable system has not been introduced in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 4A, the notification as regards the prime band is concerned`
  line `shall be limited to the carriage of two Doordarshan terrestrial channels and one regional language channel`
  line `of the State in which the network of the cable operator is located.`
  line
  line `(2) The channels referred to in sub-section (1) shall be re-transmitted without any deletion or`
  line `alteration of any programme transmitted on such channels.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the provisions of sub-section (1), any notification issued by the Central`
  line `Government or the Prasar Bharti (Broadcasting Corporation of India) in pursuance of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), prior to the 25th day of October, 2011 shall continue to remain in force till such`
  line `notifications are rescinded or amended, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9057)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Use of standard equipment in cable television network.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9057&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No cable operator shall, on and from`
  line `the date of the expiry of a period of three years from the date of the establishment and publication of the`
  line `Indian Standard by the Bureau of Indian Standards in accordance with the provisions of the Bureau of`
  line `Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986), use any ^1`
  line `[equipment or digital addressable system] in his cable`
  line `television network unless such ^1`
  line `[equipment or digital addressable system] conforms to the said Indian`
  line Standard.
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2011 s. 7, for "equipment" (w.e.f.25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9058)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Cable television network not to interfere with any telecommunication system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9058&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every cable`
  line `operator shall ensure that the cable television network being operated by him does not interfere, in any`
  line `way, with the functioning of the authorised telecommunication systems`
  line ^1
  line `[and is in conformity with such`
  line `standards relating to interference as may be prescribed by the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (9059)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 13
  title `Inspection of cable network and services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9059&sectionno=10A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line ^4
  line `[10A. Inspection of cable network and services.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions`
  line `contained in the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) or any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `Central Government or its officers authorised by it or authorised agency shall have the right to inspect the`
  line `cable network and services.`
  line
  line `(2) No prior permission or intimation shall be required to exercise the right of the Central`
  line `Government or its authorised representatives to carry out such inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) The inspection shall ordinarily be carried out after giving reasonable notice except in`
  line `circumstances where giving of such a notice shall defeat the purpose of the inspection.`
  line
  line `(4) On being so directed by the Central Government or its authorised officers oragency so authorised`
  line `by it, the cable operator shall provide the necessary equipment, services and facilities at designated place`
  line `or places for lawful interception or continuous monitoring of the cable service at its own cost by or under`
  line `the supervision of the Central Government or its officers or agency so authorised by it].`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9060)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to seize equipment used for operating cable television network.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid.,for section 11 (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9060&sectionno=11&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[11. Power to seize equipment used for operating cable television network.--If any authorised`
  line `officer has reason to believe that the provisions of section 3, section 4A, section 5,section 6, section 8,`
  line `section 9 or section 10 have been or are being contravened by any cable operator, he may seize the`
  line `equipment being used by such cable operator for operating the cable television network:`
  line
  line `Provided that the seizure of equipment in case of contravention of sections 5 and 6 shall be limited to`
  line `the programming service provided on the channel generated at the level of the cable operator.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9061)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title Confiscation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9061&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The equipment seized under sub-section (1) of section 11 shall be liable to`
  line `confiscation unless the cable operator from whom the equipment has been seized registers himself as a`
  line `cable operator under section 4 within a period of thirty days from the date of seizure of the said`
  line equipment.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9062)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `Seizure or confiscation of equipment not to interfere with other punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9062&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No seizure or`
  line `confiscation of equipment referred to in section 11 or section 12 shall prevent the infliction of any`
  line `punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9063)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `Giving of opportunity to the cable operator of seized equipment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9063&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order adjudicating`
  line `confiscation of the equipment referred to in section 12 shall be made unless the cable operator has been`
  line `given a notice in writing informing him of the grounds on which it is proposed to confiscate such`
  line `equipment and giving him a reasonable opportunity of making a representation in writing, within such`
  line `reasonable time as may be specified in the notice against the confiscation and if he so desires of being`
  line `heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that where no such notice is given within a period of ten days from the date of the seizure of`
  line `the equipment, such equipment shall be returned after the expiry of that period to the cable operator from`
  line `whose possession it was seized.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) shall, so far as may be, apply to every proceeding referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9064)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9064&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision of the court adjudicating a confiscation of`
  line `the equipment may prefer an appeal to the court to which an appeal lies from the decision of such court.`
  line
  line `(2) The appellate court may, after giving the appellant an opportunity of being heard, pass such order`
  line `as it thinks fit confirming, modifying or revising the decision appealed against or may send back the case`
  line `with such directions as it may think fit for a fresh decision or adjudication, as the case may be, after`
  line `taking additional evidence if necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) No further appeal shall lie against the order of the court made under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9065)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `Penalty for contravention of provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule, for CHAPTER IV (w.e.f. 3-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9065&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever contravenes any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall be liable,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the first contravention with advisory, or censure, or warning, or a penalty which may`
  line `extend to twenty thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) for every subsequent contravention within a period of three years, with advisory, or censure,`
  line `or warning, or a penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both,`
  line `by such designated officer, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The designated officer, may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, by order, impose penalty`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases of more than three contraventions over a period of three years, the designated`
  line `officer, in addition to penalty referred to in sub-section (1), may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `by order, suspend or revoke the registration granted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no order by the designated officer under this sub-section shall be made without`
  line `giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever aggrieved by the order made under sub-section (2), may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India or such other officer authorised by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such appeal shall be admissible after the expiry of thirty days from the date of`
  line `receipt of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an appeal may be entertained after the expiry of the period of thirty days, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9066)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9066&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9067)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 2000, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9067&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act except upon a complaint in writing made ^1`
  line `[by anyauthorised officer].`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9068)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to prohibit transmission of certain programmes in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9068&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where ^1`
  line [any
  line `authorised officer], thinks it necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, he may, by order,`
  line `prohibit any cable operator from transmitting or re-transmitting ^2`
  line `[any programme or channel if, it is not in`
  line `conformity with the prescribed programme code referred to in section 5 and advertisement code referred to`
  line `in section 6 or if it is]likely to promote, on grounds of religion, race, language, caste or community or any`
  line `other ground whatsoever, disharmony or feelings of enmity, hatred or ill-will between different religious,`
  line `racial, linguistic or regional groups or castes or communities or which is likely to disturb the public`
  line tranquillity.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "any particular programme if it is" (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9069)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to prohibit operation of cable television network in public interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9069&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Where the`
  line `Central Government thinks it necessary or expedient so to do in public interest, it may prohibit the`
  line `operation of any cable television network in such areas as it may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Where the Central Government thinks it necessary or expedient so to do in the interest of the--`
  line
  line `(i) sovereignty or integrity of India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) security of India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) friendly relations of India with any foreign State; or`
  line
  line `(iv) public order, decency or morality,`
  line
  line `it may, by order, regulate or prohibit the transmission or re-transmission of any channel or programme.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Government considers that any programme of any channel is not inconformity`
  line `with the prescribed programme code referred to in section 5 or the prescribed advertisement code referred`
  line `to in section 6, it may by order, regulate or prohibit the transmission or re-transmission of such`
  line programme].
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section 20 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9070)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 21 of 2011, s.11, for "and the Consumer Protection Act, 1986" (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9070&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the Drugs and Cosmetics Act, 1940 (23 of 1940), the Pharmacy Act, 1948`
  line `(8 of 1948), the Emblems and Names (Prevention of Improper Use) Act, 1950 (12 of 1950), the Drugs`
  line `(Control) Act, 1950 (26 of 1950), the Cinematograph Act, 1952 (37 of 1952), the Drugs and Magic`
  line `Remedies (Objectionable Advertisements) Act, 1954 (21 of 1954), the Prevention of Food Adulteration`
  line `Act, 1954 (37 of 1954), the Prize Competitions Act, 1955 (42 of 1955), the Copyright Act, 1957`
  line `(14 of 1957), the Trade and Merchandise Marks, Act, 1958 (43 of 1958), the Indecent Representation of`
  line `Women (Prohibition) Act, 1986 (60 of 1986) ^1`
  line `[, the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986) and the`
  line `Telecom Regulatory Authority of India Act, 1997 (24 of 1997)].`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9071)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9071&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the eligibility criteria for different categories of cable operators under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 4;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa) the form of application, documents to be accompanied and the fees payable under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4;]`
  line
  line `^3[(aaa) the terms and conditions of registration under sub-section (6) of section4;]`
  line
  line `^4[(aaaa) the appropriate measures under sub-section (2) of section 4A for implementation of the`
  line `notification under sub-section (1) of that section;]`
  line
  line `(b) the programme code under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the advertisement code under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the form of register to be maintained by a cable operator under section 7;`
  line
  line `^4[(da) the specifications of interference standards for interfering with any telecommunication`
  line `system under section 10;]`
  line
  line `^5[(db) the designated officer under sub-section (1) of section 16;]`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for clause (aa) (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for clause (aaa) (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-10-2011).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 3-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9072)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097&sectionId=9072&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_29_41_00006_199507_1517807323097
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Cable Television Networks (Regulation) Ordinance, 1995`
  line `(Ord. 3 of 1995) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
